properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 15 at 8:59PM CST until January 18 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...DANGEROUS COLD TONIGHT...
...HEAVY SNOW EXPECTED FRIDAY THROUGH SATURDAY...

.Temperatures will fall tonight with bitter cold wind chill
temperatures expected as northwest winds continue tonight. Wind
chill values of 20 to 35 below zero are expected. Snow returns to
the forecast for Friday through Saturday, with widespread
accumulating snow, with snowfall amounts of 5 to 10 inches
possible.

* WHAT...Heavy snow possible. Total snow accumulations of 5 to 9
inches possible.

* WHERE...Iron and Ashland Counties. This includes the Tribal
Lands of the Bad River Reservation.

* WHEN...From Friday morning through Saturday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY MORNING THROUGH SATURDAY AFTERNOON
